If the optic nerve (II) or olfactory tract is interrupted, will it regenerate? <image 1> 

A. No, will not regenerate.
B. Yes, will regenerate.

A. No, will not regenerate.

The optic nerve (cranial nerve II) and the olfactory tract do not regenerate if they are interrupted. These structures are part of the central nervous system (CNS), and unlike some peripheral nerves, CNS neurons typically do not regenerate after injury.
